1. Login to Google Cloud Console

Open console.cloud.google.com and select your project.
Go to Compute Engine → VM Instances.

2. Create New Instance

Click Create Instance.
Give your VM a name.

3. Choose Boot Disk (OS)

Select:

Ubuntu / Debian (Linux VM)

Windows Server (Windows VM)

4. Select Machine Type

Choose e2-micro, which is free-tier eligible.

5. Firewall Settings

Check:

Allow HTTP

Allow HTTPS (optional)

6. Create the VM

Click Create and wait for the VM to start.

7. Connect to VM

Linux → Just click SSH (browser-based terminal opens)

Windows → Use RDP credentials generated by GCP

8. Record Configuration

Take screenshots of:

Instance details

Public IP

SSH/RDP connection
